      <h2><em>Agaricus buckmacadooi</em> “Buck’s Agaricus”</h2>
      <p>
        The Buck’s Agaricus was named after the National Mushrooms Association’s
        long time member Buck McAdoo in 2016. Toxic to humans, the Buck’s
        Agaricus smells like tar and has a wide, flat cap with a dark center. It
        can be found in partially decayed matter on the forest floor.
      </p>
