      <h2><em>Hypomyces lactifluorum</em> “Lobster Mushroom”</h2>
      <p>
        While not actually a mushroom, the parasitic ascomycete fungus grows on
        some species of mushroom and turns them a red-orange color, similar to a
        cooked lobster. The fungus attacks milk-caps and brittlegills, notably
        the chanterelle. The chanterelle is common in this region but has not
        been spotted in the Arboretum.
      </p>
